folder0 = r'D:\Apps\CO2MPAS-versions\20160329\co2mpas.natale.venv.venv\out_batch'
file0 = '05_Apr_2016_15_57_59_summaryNATALE-PASCAformat.xlsx'
infile0 = join(folder0, file0)
df0=pd.read_excel(infile0, 'summary', header=[0, 1, 2], index_col=[0], skiprows=[3])
#####################################BATCH v.1.1.0############################################################
#Gather and name the basic variables used in the report according to their name in the CO2MPAS output file
NEDC0 = df0['nedc']['prediction']['co2_emission_value']
NEDCt0 = df0['nedc']['target']['co2_emission_value']
dNEDC0 = NEDC0-NEDCt0
UDC0 = df0['nedc']['prediction']['co2_emission_UDC']
UDCt0 = df0['nedc']['target']['co2_emission_UDC']
dUDC0 = UDC0 - UDCt0
EUDC0 = df0['nedc']['prediction']['co2_emission_EUDC']
EUDCt0 = df0['nedc']['target']['co2_emission_EUDC']
dEUDC0 = EUDC0 - EUDCt0
#Obtain the case number and vehicle model from the input file
df0['vehicle'] = df0.index
cases0 = df0['vehicle'].str.split('_').str[-1].astype('int')
model0 = df0['vehicle'].str.split('_').str[0]
#Create a dataframe with this data
valuesDF0 = pd.DataFrame({'NEDC': NEDC0,'NEDCt':NEDCt0, 'dNEDC':dNEDC0,'UDC': UDC0,'UDCt':UDCt0, 'dUDC':dUDC0,'EUDC': EUDC0,'EUDCt':EUDCt0, 'dEUDC':dEUDC0,'Case':cases0,'Model':model0})   
if (valuesDF0.NEDC.count()-valuesDF0.NEDCt.count()) != 0:
    print('NOTE:',valuesDF0.NEDC.count(),'NEDC 'u'CO\u2082 values provided and',valuesDF0.NEDCt.count(),'target NEDC 'u'CO\u2082 values provided')
    print('      Reporting will continue only with cases containing all the needed input')
valuesDF0 = valuesDF0.dropna()

#Scatterplot of %error vs CO2 emission on real cars
mydict = ([('NEDC', 0), ('UDC', 1), ('EUDC', 2)])
mydict = collections.OrderedDict(mydict)
for cycle in mydict:
    if cycle == 'NEDC':
        boxcolor = 'green'
    elif cycle == 'UDC':
        boxcolor = 'blue'
    else:
        boxcolor = 'red'
    # Create a figure instance
    fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(14, 7))
    # Create an axes instance
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
    plt.scatter(valuesDF2[cycle],valuesDF2[cycle+' error [%]'], color = 'gray', label = 'synt vehicles', alpha = 0.5)
    plt.scatter(rvaluesDF3[cycle],rvaluesDF3[cycle+' error [%]'], color = boxcolor, label = 'real vehicles')
    plt.title(cycle+' CO$_2$ emission: prediction [gCO$_2$ km$^{-1}$] vs error [%]', fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel(cycle+' emission prediction [gCO$_2$ km$^{-1}$]', fontsize=16)
    plt.ylabel(cycle+" error [%]", fontsize=14)
    first_legend = plt.legend(scatterpoints=1, bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 1.), loc=1, borderaxespad=0.)
    plt.ax = plt.gca().add_artist(first_legend)
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', which='major', labelsize=16)
    ax.tick_params(axis='y', which='major', labelsize=16)
    ax.set_ylim(-10,10)
    ax.axhline(y=5, color='black', linestyle='--')
    line1 = ax.axhline(y=-5, color='black', linestyle='--',label='± 5 %')
    ax.get_xaxis().tick_bottom()
    ax.get_yaxis().tick_left()
    ax.set_xlim(80, 240)
    plt.legend(handles=[line1], loc = 3)
    plt.show()
    #Scatterplot of error vs CO2 emission on real cars in g/km
    fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(14, 7))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111)
